RTL / schematic representation of the FIFO design.

waveform.png

Simulation waveform showing FIFO write, read, full, and empty behavior.

Conclusion

This project implements a parameterized Asynchronous FIFO in Verilog for reliable data transfer between two different clock domains.
The design uses Gray code pointers, two-stage synchronization, and full/empty protection logic to safely handle asynchronous read and write operations.

It is a good project for understanding:

FIFO architecture
CDC handling
practical Verilog design for FPGA / VLSI applications
